INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (18,2,'2014-07-02 20:47:04','2014-07-02 20:47:04','Our angelic swaddle is the product of a “dream” that creator Jill Ruse had shortly after her grand daughter Katia was born.\r\n“It was the begining of the holiday season when my first grandchild was brought to our home. I felt truly blessed. I had purchased a bassinet for her to be comfy and cozy during her visits.”\r\nAs they put Katia in the bassinet, Ms. Ruse’s step-son and his wife carefully rolled up towels and rested them closely to the baby’s body. Jill asked why and they told her the doctors said they want her to lie on her back and not roll over.\r\n“As I looked at her lying there in the bassinet, she looked like an angel. The image of her innocence and the purity was so strong in my mind. I kept thinking about how special she is and wondered what will be her journey in life.” And then Jill silently said, “Angels on your pillow sweet Katia.” The saying of “Angels on your pillow” is a wish that Jill’s best friend Astrid Merriman has said to her loved ones for many many years to remind them that their angels are watching over them.\r\nTwo nights after Katia and her family had visited, Ms. Ruse woke up with an “image” of a bed with wings for infants. She thought, “What could be better than comforting your infant in a soft comfortable swaddle that had a roll all around their body and head for support and have them wrapped with angel wings?” The idea for Angels on My Pillow was born. “My angels, and yes I talk to my angels at night, had given me the gift and I want to pass it on.” \r\nWe would love every parent to see their child as a beautiful little angel who is loved, guided, and protected by them.','About','','publish','open','open','','about','','','2014-11-19 04:38:15','2014-11-19 04:38:15','',0,'http://aomp.wpengine.com/?page_id=18',0,'page','',0);
